CatDescriptText: Mrs. Joan Charlie, 611 Morgan Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 7, 1957, pg.3 with question: "Do you think it justifiable for residents to "put the finger" (notify law enforcement officers) on rackets if they exist in their respective communities?" answer reads: "Yes because rackets are a bad influence on the children."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Joan Charlie wearing dark coat with toggle buttons, and light colored leaf patterned scarf, standing on sidewalk next to parking lot with Plymouth car with 1957 license plate "153 367," and Downtown in background
